## 8) Odtwarzanie plikÃ³w z base64 (offline) ðŸ§°

W sekcji **BUNDLE (base64)** kaÅ¼dy plik binarny jest zapisany jako:
- nagÅ‚Ã³wek `BUNDLE_FILE: <Å›cieÅ¼ka> | SHA256: ... | SIZE: ...`
- blok ```base64 ... ```

### Minimalny skrypt (Python 3) do odtworzenia
Skopiuj do `restore_bundle.py` obok tego pliku i uruchom:
```bash
python restore_bundle.py VNEIL_SVNE_ALLINONE_OFFLINE.md out_dir
```

```python
import base64, hashlib, os, re, sys

BUNDLE_HDR = re.compile(r"^### BUNDLE_FILE: (.+?) \| SHA256: ([0-9a-f]{64}) \| SIZE: (\d+)\s*$")
START = "```base64"
END = "```"

def sha256_bytes(b: bytes) -> str:
    h = hashlib.sha256()
    h.update(b)
    return h.hexdigest()

def main(src_md: str, out_dir: str):
    os.makedirs(out_dir, exist_ok=True)
    with open(src_md, "r", encoding="utf-8", errors="ignore") as f:
        lines = f.read().splitlines()

    i = 0
    extracted = 0
    while i < len(lines):
        m = BUNDLE_HDR.match(lines[i].strip())
        if not m:
            i += 1
            continue

        rel, want_hash, want_size = m.group(1), m.group(2), int(m.group(3))
        # find base64 block
        i += 1
        while i < len(lines) and lines[i].strip() != START:
            i += 1
        if i >= len(lines):
            raise RuntimeError(f"Missing base64 start for {rel}")
        i += 1

        b64_lines = []
        while i < len(lines) and lines[i].strip() != END:
            b64_lines.append(lines[i].strip())
            i += 1
        if i >= len(lines):
            raise RuntimeError(f"Missing base64 end for {rel}")

        raw = base64.b64decode("".join(b64_lines))
        if len(raw) != want_size:
            raise RuntimeError(f"Size mismatch for {rel}: got {len(raw)} expected {want_size}")
        got_hash = sha256_bytes(raw)
        if got_hash != want_hash:
            raise RuntimeError(f"Hash mismatch for {rel}: got {got_hash} expected {want_hash}")

        out_path = os.path.join(out_dir, rel)
        os.makedirs(os.path.dirname(out_path), exist_ok=True)
        with open(out_path, "wb") as wf:
            wf.write(raw)
        extracted += 1

        i += 1

    print(f"OK â€” extracted {extracted} files into {out_dir}")

if __name__ == "__main__":
    if len(sys.argv) != 3:
        print("Usage: python restore_bundle.py <allinone.md> <out_dir>")
        sys.exit(2)
    main(sys.argv[1], sys.argv[2])
```

## 0F) NARZÄ˜DZIE LOKALNE: export2delta.py (generator deltaâ€‘log + Merkle) ðŸ› ï¸

```python
#!/usr/bin/env python3
# export2delta.py - NDA-safe delta-log generator for ChatGPT exports (stdlib-only)
#
# Inputs:
#   - export .zip from ChatGPT (preferred)
#   - directory containing conversations.json / chat.html
#   - direct path to conversations.json
#
# Outputs (in --out dir):
#   - delta_log_private.md
#   - merkle_root.txt
#   - delta_log_private.sha256
#
# Modes:
#   --mode hash_only (default): store only hashes of message content
#   --mode preview           : hashes + short sanitized preview
#   --mode full              : full content (use with extreme caution)

from __future__ import annotations
import argparse, datetime, hashlib, json, re, zipfile
from pathlib import Path
from typing import Any, Dict, List, Optional, Tuple

def sha256_hex(data: bytes) -> str:
    return hashlib.sha256(data).hexdigest()

def norm_newlines(s: str) -> str:
    return s.replace("\r\n", "\n").replace("\r", "\n")

def sanitize_preview(text: str, limit: int = 80) -> str:
    t = re.sub(r"[\x00-\x08\x0b\x0c\x0e-\x1f]", "", text)
    t = re.sub(r"\s+", " ", t).strip()
    return (t[:limit].rstrip() + "â€¦") if len(t) > limit else t

def merkle_root_hex(leaves: List[str]) -> str:
    if not leaves:
        return sha256_hex(b"")
    level = [bytes.fromhex(h) for h in leaves]
    while len(level) > 1:
        if len(level) % 2 == 1:
            level.append(level[-1])
        nxt = []
        for i in range(0, len(level), 2):
            nxt.append(hashlib.sha256(level[i] + level[i+1]).digest())
        level = nxt
    return level[0].hex()

def load_export(path: Path) -> Tuple[Optional[List[Dict[str, Any]]], Dict[str, Any]]:
    meta: Dict[str, Any] = {"source": str(path)}
    if path.is_file() and path.suffix.lower() == ".zip":
        with zipfile.ZipFile(path, "r") as z:
            names = z.namelist()
            conv_name = next((n for n in names if n.endswith("conversations.json")), None)
            if conv_name:
                meta["conversations_json"] = conv_name
                data = json.loads(z.read(conv_name).decode("utf-8", errors="replace"))
                return data, meta
            chat_name = next((n for n in names if n.endswith("chat.html")), None)
            if chat_name:
                meta["chat_html"] = chat_name
                meta["chat_html_sha256"] = sha256_hex(z.read(chat_name))
                return None, meta
        return None, meta

    if path.is_dir():
        conv = path / "conversations.json"
        if conv.exists():
            meta["conversations_json"] = str(conv)
            data = json.loads(conv.read_text(encoding="utf-8", errors="replace"))
            return data, meta
        chat = path / "chat.html"
        if chat.exists():
            meta["chat_html"] = str(chat)
            meta["chat_html_sha256"] = sha256_hex(chat.read_bytes())
            return None, meta
        return None, meta

    if path.is_file() and path.name == "conversations.json":
        meta["conversations_json"] = str(path)
        data = json.loads(path.read_text(encoding="utf-8", errors="replace"))
        return data, meta

    return None, meta

def extract_messages(convs: List[Dict[str, Any]]) -> List[Dict[str, Any]]:
    out: List[Dict[str, Any]] = []
    for c in convs:
        cid = c.get("id") or ""
        title = c.get("title") or ""
        mapping = c.get("mapping") or {}
        for node in mapping.values():
            msg = (node or {}).get("message")
            if not msg:
                continue
            role = ((msg.get("author") or {}).get("role") or "")
            ct = msg.get("create_time") or msg.get("timestamp") or None
            content = msg.get("content") or {}
            parts = content.get("parts") or []
            txt = "\n".join([p for p in parts if isinstance(p, str)])
            if not txt.strip():
                continue
            out.append({
                "conversation_id": cid,
                "title": title,
                "role": role,
                "create_time": ct,
                "text": norm_newlines(txt),
            })
    def key(m):
        ct = m.get("create_time")
        return ct if isinstance(ct, (int, float)) else 0
    out.sort(key=key)
    return out

def fmt_time(ct: Any) -> str:
    if isinstance(ct, (int, float)):
        try:
            return datetime.datetime.fromtimestamp(ct, tz=datetime.timezone.utc).isoformat()
        except Exception:
            return str(ct)
    return str(ct) if ct is not None else ""

def main() -> int:
    ap = argparse.ArgumentParser()
    ap.add_argument("input", help="Path to export .zip, directory, or conversations.json")
    ap.add_argument("--out", default=".", help="Output directory")
    ap.add_argument("--mode", choices=["hash_only", "preview", "full"], default="hash_only")
    ap.add_argument("--filter-conversation", default=None, help="Optional conversation_id to include only one")
    args = ap.parse_args()

    inp = Path(args.input).expanduser().resolve()
    outdir = Path(args.out).expanduser().resolve()
    outdir.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)

    convs, meta = load_export(inp)
    lines: List[str] = []
    leaves: List[str] = []

    lines.append("# PRIVATE DELTA-LOG (generated locally)\n\n")
    lines.append(f"- source: {meta.get('source')}\n")
    if meta.get("conversations_json"):
        lines.append(f"- conversations_json: {meta['conversations_json']}\n")
    if meta.get("chat_html"):
        lines.append(f"- chat_html: {meta['chat_html']}\n")
        lines.append(f"- chat_html_sha256: {meta.get('chat_html_sha256','')}\n")
    lines.append(f"- mode: {args.mode}\n\n---\n\n")

    if convs is None:
        payload = (meta.get("chat_html_sha256") or "").encode("utf-8")
        leaf = sha256_hex(payload)
        leaves = [leaf]
        lines.append("## OPAQUE EXPORT PROOF\n\n")
        lines.append("Nie znaleziono `conversations.json`; zapisano hash `chat.html`.\n\n")
        lines.append(f"- leaf_sha256: `{leaf}`\n")
    else:
        msgs = extract_messages(convs)
        if args.filter_conversation:
            msgs = [m for m in msgs if m.get("conversation_id") == args.filter_conversation]

        current_conv = None
        for m in msgs:
            cid = m["conversation_id"]
            title = m.get("title") or ""
            if cid != current_conv:
                current_conv = cid
                lines.append(f"\n## Conversation {cid}\n")
                if title:
                    lines.append(f"**Title:** {title}\n")
                lines.append("\n")

            role = m.get("role") or ""
            t = fmt_time(m.get("create_time"))
            txt = m.get("text") or ""
            txt_hash = sha256_hex(txt.encode("utf-8", errors="replace"))
            leaf_material = f"{cid}|{role}|{t}|{txt_hash}".encode("utf-8")
            leaf = sha256_hex(leaf_material)
            leaves.append(leaf)

            if args.mode == "hash_only":
                lines.append(f"- {t} | {role} | text_sha256=`{txt_hash}` | leaf=`{leaf}`\n")
            elif args.mode == "preview":
                prev = sanitize_preview(txt, 80)
                lines.append(f"- {t} | {role} | preview=\"{prev}\" | text_sha256=`{txt_hash}` | leaf=`{leaf}`\n")
            else:
                lines.append(f"### {t} | {role}\n\n")
                lines.append("```\n" + txt + "\n```\n")
                lines.append(f"text_sha256=`{txt_hash}`  leaf=`{leaf}`\n\n")

    root = merkle_root_hex(leaves)
    lines.append("\n---\n\n")
    lines.append(f"## MERKLE ROOT\n\n- merkle_root_sha256: `{root}`\n")
    lines.append(f"- leaf_count: {len(leaves)}\n")

    md = "".join(lines)
    md_path = outdir / "delta_log_private.md"
    md_path.write_text(md, encoding="utf-8")
    (outdir / "merkle_root.txt").write_text(root + "\n", encoding="utf-8")
    (outdir / "delta_log_private.sha256").write_text(sha256_hex(md.encode("utf-8")) + "\n", encoding="utf-8")

    print(f"Wygenerowano: {md_path}")
    print(f"Merkle root: {root}")
    return 0

if __name__ == "__main__":
    raise SystemExit(main())
```
